{"word":"H2686 - חָצַץ - châtsats - khaw-tsats' - Archer","slug":"H2686","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">חָצַץ</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>châtsats"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>khaw-tsats'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Archer"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D7;&#x05E6;&#x05E5; - cha&#x0302;tsats</b> - <i>khaw-tsats'</i><p/>A primitive root (compare <a href=\"#/H2673\">H2673</a>); properly to <i>chop</i> into, pierce or sever; hence to <i>curtail</i>, to <i>distribute</i> (into ranks); as denominative from <a href=\"#/H2671\">H2671</a>; to <i>shoot</i> an arrow: - archer, X bands, cut off in the midst."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H2671\">H2671</a>, <a href=\"#/H2687\">H2687</a>, <a href=\"#/H2688\">H2688</a>"}]}